Parliament, Thursday, 2 March 2023 – The Portfolio Committee on Forestry, Fisheries and Environment will from tomorrow visit KwaZulu-Natal to conduct public hearings on the Climate Change Bill.
	
	The Bill seeks to ensure the effective management of inevitable climate change impacts by enhancing adaptive capacity, strengthening resilience and reducing vulnerability to climate change, with a view to building social, economic and environmental resilience and an adequate national adaptation response in the context of global climate change responses.
	
	The committee invites all interested citizens and organisations to attend the public hearings and comment on the Climate Change Bill.
	
	Details of the public hearings are as follows:
	Date: 3 March (Friday)
	Time: 10H00
	Venue: Stanger Town Hall (KwaDukuza Local Municipality)
	
	Date: 4 March (Saturday)
	Time: 10H00
	Venue: Pietermaritzburg Town Hall (Umsunduzi Local Municipality)
	
	Date: 5 March (Sunday)
	Time: 10H00
	Venue: Westville Civic Centre (EThekwini Metropolitan Municipality)
	
	For media enquiries or interviews with the committee Chairperson, please contact:
